Function Reference/merge filters « WordPress Codex
-----------

!!! THIS FUNCTION DOES NOT EXISTS ANYMORE !!!

Old documentation :

Merge the filter functions of a specific filter hook with generic filter
functions.

It is possible to defined generic filter functions using the filter hook
*all*. These functions are called for every filter tag. This function
merges the functions attached to the *all* hook with the functions of a
specific hook defined by `$tag`.

Usage
-----

`  <?php merge_filters($tag); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$tag` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The filter hook of which the functions should be
    merged.
    Default: *None*

